## 🚀 Feature Proposal

In the case of stream processing, workSheetReader parses mergeCell and outputs the information of the merged cells
## Motivation

I have a huge table, approximately 70M+, so I have to use stream parsing for the table. However, I found that in this case, I can't obtain the information of the merged cells inside the table

## Example

 const reader = new ExcelJS.stream.xlsx.WorkbookReader(path, {
    entries: "emit",
    sharedStrings: "cache",
    styles: "cache", 
    worksheets: "emit",
  });
  for await (const worksheetReader of reader) {
    worksheetReader.on("mergeCell", (mergeCell) => {
      console.log("--->mergeCell", mergeCell);
    });
    for await (const row of worksheetReader) {
      yield {
        sheet: worksheetReader.name,
        index: row.number,
        values: row.values,
        cellCount: row.cellCount,
        firstCell: row.getCell(1),
        cell(col) {
          return row.getCell(col);
        },
        each(fn) {
          for (let col = 1; col <= row.cellCount; col++) {
            fn(row.getCell(col), col);
          }
        },
      };
    }
  }
